ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Shannon Diversity species diversity index, a measure diversity of microbiome
Operational Taxonomic Richness species population index, a measure diversity of microbiome
Prevalence of the allele APOE3 (Apolipoprotein E, allele 3)
Prevalence of the allele APOE2 (Apolipoprotein E, allele 2)
Prevalence of the allele APOE4 (Apolipoprotein E, allele 4)
Genomic, mitochondrial or viral DNA detection
Measure of protein levels of tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNFα)
Measure of protein levels of Interleukin-1Beta (IL-1β)
Measure of protein levels of Interleukin-6 (IL-6)
Prevalence of Herpes simplex virus Type 1 Immunoglobulin G
Herpes positive status based on Immunoglobulin G (HSV1 IgG)
Prevalence of Herpes simplex virus Type 1 Immunoglobulin M
Herpes positive status based on Immunoglobulin M (HSV1 IgM)
